#: ../../manual/interface/modes.rst:3
msgid "Modes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/interface/modes.rst:5
msgid ""
"*Modes* are a Blender-level object-oriented feature, which means that *the "
"whole Blender application* is always in *one and only one mode*, and that "
"the available modes vary depending on the selected active object's type - "
"most of them only enable the default :guilabel:`Object` mode (like cameras, "
"lamps, etc.). Each mode is designed to edit an aspect of the selected "
"object. See the *Blender's Modes* table below for details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/interface/modes.rst:10
msgid "Mode selection example (mesh object)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/interface/modes.rst:13
msgid ""
"You set the current mode in the :guilabel:`Mode` drop-down list of "
":guilabel:`3D View` header (see *Mode selection example (mesh object)*)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/interface/modes.rst:19
msgid ""
"You can only select objects in :guilabel:`Object` mode. In all others, the "
"current object selection is \"locked\" (except, to some extent, with an "
"armature's :guilabel:`Pose` mode)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/interface/modes.rst:23
msgid "Modes might affect many things in Blender:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/interface/modes.rst:25
msgid ""
"They can modify the panels and/or controls available in some "
":guilabel:`Buttons` windows' contexts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/interface/modes.rst:26
msgid ""
"They can modify the behavior of whole windows, like e.g. the "
":guilabel:`UV/Image Editor` window (and obviously, :guilabel:`3D View` s!)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/interface/modes.rst:27
msgid ""
"They can modify the available header tools (menus and/or menu entries, as "
"well as other controls...). For example, in the :guilabel:`3D View` window, "
"the :guilabel:`Object` menu in :guilabel:`Object` mode changes to a "
":guilabel:`Mesh` menu in :guilabel:`Edit` mode (with an active mesh "
"object!), and a :guilabel:`Paint` menu in :guilabel:`Vertex Paint` mode..."
msgstr ""

